                <div class="Item-BodyWrap">
                    <div class="Item-Body">
                        <div class="Message userContent">
                            <p>Heyo.</p>

<p>No problem. In that case, preferrably I would like my last name to be 'Rikers'. Though Rikers R. Rikers does sound a bit odd,  I feel it rolls off the tongue pretty well, like 'M&amp;Ms', or' Starbucks', or '29th Infantry Division welcomes Rikers with open arms'.<br />
Unfortunately I will ultimately have to settle for 'Vortex R. Rikers' if that is okay with you.</p>

<p>| Folk | Arma 2 | Vortex Rikers | No Rank, (Chocolate-coated Salty Pretzel, First Class) | Preoccupied with real life, general exhaustion with video games |<br />
Arma 2 experience. I played that dumb game for too many hours than I can count, easily 500+, but I will skip describing non-unit experience. I used to play with a community called Folk, more than 2 years ago, definitely more.  It was a laid back, casual unit with no ranks to speak of, you generally had just a handful of people responsible for organizing and hosting missions, and the rest were simply players occupying their preferred slot.<br />
I don't recall using any mods, it was mostly a vanilla Arma 2 experience. However actually participating was anything but casual, the unit adhered to pretty realistic standards; chain of command, proper communication between squad members, you didn't have people talking who were out of action, squads were always organized and doing their jobs, among many other things. The average session had over 60 people usually all participating and coordinating very well, with missions usually taking an hour or two. It was mostly a vs AI deal, however there would be at least one pvp mission during the usual day. <br />
Though like I said there weren't any ranks, I have participated for many months, probably a solid year, usually as a basic, or anti tank rifleman, or in support of one, although due to the flexible nature of the unit it wasn't rare to take on other roles as needed. All of this was really only possible by having a great community of ( mostly ) responsible and ( mostly ) sane individuals. I have no clue what's going on with it right now, only that it merged with another community and is now called Folk ARPS some years ago.<br />
Having said all of that, I would very much like to try a more realistic experience with Arma 3.<br />
I left the unit due to having no more free time to dedicate to it, or video games in general, and was completely burned out of Arma 2.</p>

<p>If I'm accepted I would very much prefer option B, 7-8pm GMT sounds a lot easier to schedule around.</p>
                        </div>
